\begin{document}

\section*{Description of the LLM Quality Scoring Method}

The LLM (Language Model) quality scoring method is designed to objectively assess the quality of a given conversational input or task. This method utilizes a structured and detailed scoring system, broken down into several specific criteria, to provide a quantitative evaluation of the quality. Each criterion is rated on a scale from 0 to 5, where 0 indicates the lowest quality and 5 indicates the highest quality.

\subsection*{Criteria}

\begin{itemize}
    \item \textbf{Clarity (clarity)}
    \begin{itemize}
        \item \textbf{Definition}: Whether the input is expressed clearly, easily understood, and avoids ambiguity or misinterpretation.
        \item \textbf{Scoring Range}: 0 (least clear) to 5 (most clear).
    \end{itemize}

    \item \textbf{Relevance (relevance)}
    \begin{itemize}
        \item \textbf{Definition}: Whether the input is relevant to its context and user intent, ensuring directness and urgency of the question.
        \item \textbf{Scoring Range}: 0 (least relevant) to 5 (most relevant).
    \end{itemize}

    \item \textbf{Conciseness (conciseness)}
    \begin{itemize}
        \item \textbf{Definition}: Whether the input is concise, with no redundant information or extraneous details.
        \item \textbf{Scoring Range}: 0 (least concise) to 5 (most concise).
    \end{itemize}

    \item \textbf{Specificity (specificity)}
    \begin{itemize}
        \item \textbf{Definition}: Whether the input is specific and concrete, avoiding vague concepts or generalizations.
        \item \textbf{Scoring Range}: 0 (least specific) to 5 (most specific).
    \end{itemize}

    \item \textbf{Context Provision (context\_provision)}
    \begin{itemize}
        \item \textbf{Definition}: Whether the input provides necessary background information to support the accuracy and relevance of the response.
        \item \textbf{Scoring Range}: 0 (provides no context) to 5 (provides comprehensive context).
    \end{itemize}

    \item \textbf{Logical Coherence (logical\_coherence)}
    \begin{itemize}
        \item \textbf{Definition}: Whether the input is logically coherent, maintaining internal logic and consistency.
        \item \textbf{Scoring Range}: 0 (least coherent) to 5 (most coherent).
    \end{itemize}

    \item \textbf{Engagement (engagement)}
    \begin{itemize}
        \item \textbf{Definition}: Whether the input is engaging, capable of sparking discussion or deeper reflection.
        \item \textbf{Scoring Range}: 0 (least engaging) to 5 (most engaging).
    \end{itemize}

    \item \textbf{Neutrality (neutrality)}
    \begin{itemize}
        \item \textbf{Definition}: Whether the input is neutral, unbiased, and does not lead to specific conclusions.
        \item \textbf{Scoring Range}: 0 (least neutral) to 5 (most neutral).
    \end{itemize}

    \item \textbf{Grammatical Accuracy and Language Use (grammatical\_accuracy\_and\_language\_use)}
    \begin{itemize}
        \item \textbf{Definition}: Whether the input adheres to grammatical rules and uses appropriate language expression.
        \item \textbf{Scoring Range}: 0 (poor grammar and language use) to 5 (excellent grammar and language use).
    \end{itemize}

    \item \textbf{Creativity (creativity)}
    \begin{itemize}
        \item \textbf{Definition}: Whether the input demonstrates innovation, posing novel and interesting questions.
        \item \textbf{Scoring Range}: 0 (least creative) to 5 (most creative).
    \end{itemize}
\end{itemize}

\subsection*{Scoring Process}

\begin{itemize}
    \item \textbf{Input Processing}: The input is analyzed to determine its characteristics in relation to each of the ten criteria.
    \item \textbf{Scoring}: Each criterion is assigned a score between 0 and 5 based on the input's characteristics.
    \item \textbf{Output}: The scores for each criterion are compiled and returned using the "final\_result" tool. The output is a simple list of scores without any additional text or explanation.
\end{itemize}

This method ensures a systematic and objective evaluation of the quality of conversational inputs, providing a clear and quantifiable measure that can be used for further analysis and improvement of the language model's performance.

\end{document}
